1. Copy allCountries.zip, Weather.csv and scripts to CDH local system.

2. Unzip allCountries.zip archive:
	unzip allCountries.zip
	
3. Run commands to write data on HDFS:
	hadoop fs -mkdir /user/cloudera/weather-analytics
	hadoop fs -mkdir /user/cloudera/weather-analytics/input
	hadoop fs -put allCountries.txt Weather.csv /user/cloudera/weather-analytics/input

4. To create tables in the Impala:
	impala-shell -f creating_static_tables.sql
	
5. Change access to HDFS folders for Impala:
	sudo -u hdfs hadoop fs -chown -R impala:supergroup /user/hive/warehouse/weather_analytics.db/weather
	sudo -u hdfs hadoop fs -chown -R impala:supergroup /user/hive/warehouse/weather_analytics.db/countries
	
6. Run commands:
	impala-shell -f loading_static_data.sql
	
	impala-shell -f task1.sql
	NOTE: The result of the operation will be stored in a unique_stations table.

	impala-shell -f task2.sql
	NOTE: The result of the operation will be stored in a weather_with_country table.
	
	impala-shell -f task3.sql
	NOTE: Results of the operation will be stored in weather_analytics_by_date and weather_analytics_total tables.